targets.rawSql: SELECT countInProgress AS "Items in Progress", date_queried AS "Date" FROM aspenhealthcare_DB.unprocessed_items

panels.description: Allows you to see precise figures on items that were processed. It enables you to assess whether your queue items are failing or not. Please note that for failed items that were retried, each retry status is taken into account.

targets.rawSql: SELECT countSuccessful AS "Successful", countBusinessExceptions AS "Business Exceptions", countApplicationExceptions AS "Application Exceptions", date_queried AS "Date" FROM aspenhealthcare_DB.transactions_overview

panels.title: Transactions Overview

targets.rawSql:
SELECT 
    ((countSuccessful) * 1.0 / ((countSuccessful) + (countBusinessExceptions) + (countApplicationExceptions)) * 100) AS success_rate_percentage
FROM 
    aspenhealthcare_DB.transactions_overview
ORDER BY date_queried DESC
LIMIT 2

panels.description: Displays the number of processes that's pending for more than 30 mins

targets.rawSql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS "ProcessesOverLimit"
FROM (
  SELECT averagePendingTimeInSeconds
  FROM aspenhealthcare_DB.process_details_table
  WHERE averagePendingTimeInSeconds > 1800
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT averagePendingTimeInSeconds
  FROM italtile_DB.process_details_table
  WHERE averagePendingTimeInSeconds > 1800
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT averagePendingTimeInSeconds
  FROM afgriprod_DB.process_details_table
  WHERE averagePendingTimeInSeconds > 1800

  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT averagePendingTimeInSeconds
  FROM intellicomms_DB.process_details_table
  WHERE averagePendingTimeInSeconds > 1800

  UNION ALL

  SELECT averagePendingTimeInSeconds
  FROM tangentsolutionsproduction_DB.process_details_table
  WHERE averagePendingTimeInSeconds > 1800

) AS OverLimit

panels.title: Pending > 30 min

panels.description: (countErrors / (countSuccessful + countErrors + countStopped)) * 100 AS error_rate aggregated over all tenants

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
    'Aspenhealthcare' AS db_name,
    (countErrors / (countSuccessful + countErrors + countStopped)) * 100 AS error_rate
FROM
    (SELECT * 
     FROM aspenhealthcare_DB.completed_jobs_overview 
     ORDER BY date_queried DESC 
     LIMIT 1) AS latest_aspen

UNION ALL

SELECT
    'Italtile' AS db_name,
    (countErrors / (countSuccessful + countErrors + countStopped)) * 100 AS error_rate
FROM
    (SELECT * 
     FROM italtile_DB.completed_jobs_overview 
     ORDER BY date_queried DESC 
     LIMIT 1) AS latest_italtile



UNION ALL

SELECT
    'Afgri' AS db_name,
    (countErrors / (countSuccessful + countErrors + countStopped)) * 100 AS error_rate
FROM
    (SELECT * 
     FROM afgriprod_DB.completed_jobs_overview 
     ORDER BY date_queried DESC 
     LIMIT 1) AS latest_afgri

UNION ALL

SELECT
    'Intellicoms' AS db_name,
    (countErrors / (countSuccessful + countErrors + countStopped)) * 100 AS error_rate
FROM
    (SELECT * 
     FROM intellicomms_DB.completed_jobs_overview 
     ORDER BY date_queried DESC 
     LIMIT 1) AS latest_Intellicoms

UNION ALL

SELECT
    'TangentSolutions Production' AS db_name,
    (countErrors / (countSuccessful + countErrors + countStopped)) * 100 AS error_rate
FROM
    (SELECT * 
     FROM tangentsolutionsproduction_DB.completed_jobs_overview 
     ORDER BY date_queried DESC 
     LIMIT 1) AS latest_TanProd

ORDER BY db_name;

panels.title: Fault Rate across Tenants (%)

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
    Process_name,
    COUNT(*) AS Failure_Count
FROM
    global.faulted_jobs
GROUP BY
    Process_name

ORDER BY
    Failure_Count DESC;

SELECT
    Process_name,
    Organization,
    Folder,
    Started,
    Reason,
    
    TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, Started, Ended) AS runtime_seconds
FROM
    global.faulted_jobs
ORDER BY Started DESC;
SELECT HostMachineName, MaintenanceMode FROM global.maintenance_mode_states WHERE MaintenanceMode = "Enabled"
SELECT Folder, Name FROM global.disabled_triggers
